.TH "core_kernel_data" 9 "core_kernel_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
core_kernel_data \- tell if addr points to kernel data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" core_kernel_data
.BI "(unsigned long addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
address to test
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns true if \fIaddr\fP passed in is from the core kernel data
section.
.SH "NOTE"
On some archs it may return true for core RODATA, and false
for others. But will always be true for core RW data.
